html
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1')
    title Fast Loading Webfonts

    link(rel='stylesheet', type='text/css', href='build/build.css')

  body

    article

      section
        h1 Fast Loading Web fonts

      section(data-bespoke-hash='outline')
        h2.bullet Outline
        ul
          li Why Web fonts make the web better?
          li What is a Web font?
          li Stats
          li WOFF 1.0
          li WOFF 2.0

      section
        h2 Why talk about Web fonts?
        ul
          li Won a ticket to go to <a href="http://velocityconf.com/velocity2014">Velocity 2014</a> via the <a href="http://davidwalsh.name/">David Walsh Blog</a>
          li One of my favourite talks was <a href="https://docs.google.com/a/funnelcity.com/presentation/d/10QJ_GABjwzfwUb5DZ3DULdv82k74QdPArkovYJZ-glc/present#slide=id.p19">Making Web Fonts Fast(er)</a> by <a href="https://twitter.com/igrigorik">@igrigorik</a>

      section
        h2.bullet What is a Web font?
        ul
          li Glyph = vector shape
          li Font = collection of glyphs
          li Font variants (bold, italic, condensed, etc.)
          li Font file size determined by
            ul
              li Complexity of the glyphs
              li Number of glyphs

      section
        h2.bullet Why Web fonts make the web better?
        ul
          li Accessible
          li Easier to read
          li Copy + Paste
          li SEO friendly
          li Zoom in and out
          li Beautiful

      section(data-bespoke-state='emphatic')
        h2 Most mobile devices ship with only one system font
        h3 Web fonts are here to stay!

      section
        h2 Interesting Statistics
        h3 According to HTTP archive
        ul
          li 35% of the <a href="http://httparchive.org/urls.php?start=1&end=10000">Alexa's</a> TOP 1000 web sites are using web fonts on their homepage
          li 62% when we look beyond the homepage of these websites


      section
        h2 Interesting Statistics
        div.normal-image
          <img src="images/webfont-trend.png">
        ul
          li This <a href="http://httparchive.org/trends.php#perFonts">chart</a> shows the percentage of sites that make at least one request for a custom font (Sep 2013-2014)
          li Over 230% growth in one year
          li Check out <a href="https://www.google.com/fonts#Analytics:total">Google fonts usage</a> real-time data


      section
        h2 Web fonts in Browsers
        ul
          li Impacts user experience
          li IE renders immediately with fallback and re-renders when font is available
          li Firefox blocks text rendering for up to 3s and uses fallback if timeout is reached
          li Chrome M35+ recently added a 3 second timeout
          li Older versions of Chrome and Safari block text rendering indefinitely


      section
        h1.bullet WOFF 1.0
        ul
          li Web Open Font Format
          li Supported by <a href="http://caniuse.com/#search=woff" target="_blank">"all"</a> browsers

      section
        h1.bullet WOFF 2.0
        ul
          li Font compression format announced in April 2012 after a year or so of exploration
          li Faster decompression speed and lower memory requirements
          li Bleeding edge &rarr; <a href="http://caniuse.com/#search=woff2">limited support</a>

        <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p>Chrome 36 and Opera 23 (both stable) already support WOFF2 web fonts: <a href="http://t.co/RN1wVrv63B">http://t.co/RN1wVrv63B</a> Convert your web fonts to improve performance.</p>&mdash; Mathias Bynens (@mathias) <a href="https://twitter.com/mathias/status/501721357785522176">August 19, 2014</a></blockquote>
        <script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>

      section
        h2 Why use WOFF2?
        ul
          li It offers a 30% average gain over WOFF 1.0 (measured using Google Fonts corpus)
          li Gain was more impressive for Asian fonts where 50%+ improvements was noticed

      section
        h2.bullet What about TELUS?
        ul
          li WOFF 2.0 offers a 22.9% average gain over WOFF 1.0
          li Shave off 72 KB on initial page load

      section
        h2 TELUS web fonts
        table
          tr
            th font-family
            th woff
            th woff2
            th performance<br/>improvement
          tr
            td telusdings-regular
            td 26 KB
            td 21 KB
            td 19%
          tr
            td tultralightregular
            td 74 KB
            td 58 KB
            td 22%
          tr
            td tthinregular<br/>tultralightregular (bold)
            td 61 KB
            td 46 KB
            td 24.59%
          tr
            td tlightregular<br/>tthinregular (bold)
            td 58 KB
            td 44 KB
            td 24.14%
          tr
            td tromanregular<br/>tlightregular (bold)
            td 49 KB
            td 37 KB
            td 24.49%
          tr
            td tromanregular (bold)
            td 43 KB
            td 33 KB
            td 23.26%

      section(data-bespoke-state='emphatic')
        h1.bullet Are we using WOFF 2.0?
        ul
          li .woff2 already on static.telus.com
          li Not consumed by any of the sites yet


      section
        h2 What's needed?
            pre
              code.language-css.
                @font-face {
                  font-family: "Dings";
                  src: url(//path-to-file/dings.woff2) format('woff2'),
                       url(//path-to-file/dings.woff) format('woff'),
                       url(//path-to-file/dings.ttf) format(ttf'),
                       url(//path-to-file/dings.svg) format(svg'),
                       url(//path-to-file/dings.eot) format(eot')
                }

      section
        h2 How to generate .woff2 files?
        pre
          code.language-css.
            $ git clone https://code.google.com/p/font-compression-reference/

            $ cd font-compression-reference/woff2
            $ make clean all

            $ ./woff2_compress telusdings.ttf

         <a href="https://code.google.com/p/font-compression-reference/wiki/gathering_compression_improvement_numbers">More info &raquo;</a>

      section
        h2.bullet TL;DR
        ul

          li Web fonts popularity is going through the roof
          li Web fonts enhance the user experience but be selective when choosing fonts for a website
            ul
              li Reduce number of fonts and fonts variants
          li Optimize font delivery
            ul
              li Serve relevant characters only using the latest compression formats available


      section(data-bespoke-state='emphatic')
        h2 Questions?


